You can see that the when declaring `arr` as an pointer to an array, the two arrays of two integers are not [contiguous][1], whereas when declaring it as an array of arrays, they are. Moreover, when declaring it as an array of arrays there is no need to dynamically allocate memory (e.g., using `malloc`). 


